My [last blog post](https://www.jeffreyknox.dev/blog/building-a-javascript-documentation-website/) demonstrated how to build a JavaScript documentation website using [JSDoc](https://jsdoc.app/) and have it deployed on [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/). The process was a bit manual though so in this post I improve upon the solution by automating the build using a [GitHub Action](https://github.com/features/actions) to ensure your documentation website is never out of sync with the documentation in your code base.

